   "source": [
    "# Auto Object Detection Pipeline (YOLOv8)\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook is fully self-configuring — nothing is hardcoded to a specific\n",
    "machine, GPU count, or dataset:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Detects the project directory** it's running in\n",
    "2. **Detects every available GPU** — runs correctly on 0, 1, or N GPUs\n",
    "   (CUDA, any count) with automatic multi-GPU training, falls back to\n",
    "   Apple MPS or CPU if no CUDA GPU is present\n",
    "3. **Auto-locates your dataset** (existing `data.yaml`, or a standard\n",
    "   `images/` + `labels/` YOLO folder layout) and builds `data.yaml` if missing\n",
    "4. **Auto-selects model size, epoch budget, and batch size** from the\n",
    "   detected hardware (GPU memory) and dataset size — no fixed numbers to edit\n",
    "5. **Trains** a YOLOv8 model on the dataset, using all detected GPUs\n",
    "6. **Saves and reloads** the best weights to confirm they load cleanly\n",
    "7. **Launches a Streamlit app** with an image upload button, live bounding\n",
    "   box detection, a confidence threshold slider, and a GPU picker if more\n",
    "   than one GPU is available at inference time\n",
    "\n",
    "### Before you run\n",
    "Place your dataset anywhere under the project folder using one of these layouts:\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "dataset/\n",
    "├── data.yaml            # optional - if present, it's used as-is\n",
    "├── images/\n",
    "│   ├── train/\n",
    "│   └── val/\n",
    "└── labels/\n",
    "    ├── train/\n",
    "    └── val/\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "If you don't have a `classes.txt` / `data.yaml`, the notebook will infer the\n",
    "number of classes from your label files and name them `class0, class1, ...`\n",
    "— rename `names:` in the generated `data.yaml` afterwards if you want real\n",
    "class names.\n",
    "\n",
    "Run the cells top to bottom.\n"
   ]
  },
